      "observation": "step `upgrade_spring_boot_3_3` (jdk=17): BUILD FAILED post-recipe, rc=1\n--- first error cluster ---\n[05:01:03] PROJECT_ROOT=/work/src/./eDrops PHASE=build_post JDK=17\n[ERROR] /work/src/eDrops/src/main/kotlin/com/sigmondsmart/edrops/config/WebSecurityConfig.kt: (19, 18) Unresolved reference: antMatchers\n[ERROR] Failed to execute goal org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-maven-plugin:1.7.20:compile (compile) on project eDrops: Compilation failure\n[ERROR] /work/src/eDrops/src/main/kotlin/com/sigmondsmart/edrops/config/WebSecurityConfig.kt:[19,18] Unresolved reference: antMatchers\n[ERROR] -> [Help 1]\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] To see the full stack trace of the errors, re-run Maven with the -e switch.\n[ERROR] Re-run Maven using the -X switch to enable full debug logging.\n[ERROR] \n[ERROR] For more information about the errors and possible solutions, please read the following articles:\n[ERROR] [Help 1] http://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/MAVEN/MojoFailureException",
      "qwen_observation": "The build failed at step `upgrade_spring_boot_3_3` because the Kotlin source code uses `antMatchers`, which was removed in Spring Security 6 (part of Spring Boot 3), and the Kotlin compiler plugin version (1.7.20) is too old to compile against the new dependencies or target JDK 17/21 effectively.",
      "qwen_rationale": "The failure is twofold: 1) Spring Boot 3 migration removes `antMatchers` in favor of `requestMatchers`, which the OpenRewrite recipe should handle, but the build fails before or during that transition due to the Kotlin plugin version. 2) The observation library explicitly identifies that the Kotlin Maven Plugin is too old for the target JVM. We must insert the `bump_kotlin_plugin` step before `upgrade_build_to_java21` as instructed. Additionally, since the project is Kotlin-primary, we should ensure the Kotlin plugin is bumped early enough to handle the Spring Boot 3 changes if possible, but the library fix placement is specific. I will follow the library fix placement strictly. The `UpgradeSpringBoot_3_3` recipe should handle the `antMatchers` -> `requestMatchers` migration in Java/Kotlin sources, but the compiler needs to be new enough to process the resulting code and dependencies. The previous failure might have been because the recipe applied but the compile failed due to the old Kotlin plugin not understanding the new Spring Security API or just general incompatibility. Bumping the plugin is the required fix."
    },
